  "doc_id": "27658",
  "text": "Unlike traditional aluminum block thermal cyclers that need compatible brands of PCR tubes for effective heat transfer, water baths accept PCR vessels of almost any kind. The vessels can be simply partially-immersed into the water baths to carry out the reaction steps. The reaction will go well as long as the reagents are placed below the oil level. We used the Roche LightCycler glass capillaries (20 μL capacity) (Roche Diagnostics, Indianapolis, IN) to perform very rapid PCR reactions due to the faster heat transfer one can get over polypropylene PCR tubes [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . The high-aspect ratio geometry of the glass capillary tubes also aided the water bath to heat and cool the reagents faster.",
